,Recommended,284260,24282172,"Posted: 12 July, 2016",all,Quady14,"If I could rate a game purely based on how good it is for making desktop wallpapers, Panoramical is up there with the best. As a fun diversion to enjoy some eye-melting visual effects, it's maybe a little expensive. If you got a discount coupon for it (like I did) or see it for cheap during a sale, and just want to enjoy a trip for the eyes, go for it. Just know there's not really much interaction other than messing with 9 sliders which affect each of the 14-15 environments, (that's as many as I discovered, I don't believe there's more unless you unlock stuff through some obscure method) you can't walk or look around, so you're set only with what's in front of you. There's also an ""Inverted"" mode which just flips the colors of all the levels. Still, like I said, made some sick desktop wallpapers with it! I'll give it a thumbs up."
