,Recommended,284260,24290352,"Posted: 13 July, 2016",all,Hathor,"Steam popped up recommending this game and as a huge fan of Proteus I had to check it out.  Although I had some trouble getting the MIDI controls working (it seems to have major issues if you have more than one MIDI controller hooked up), once I got everything synced up to my Arturia Spark I really started having a lot of fun with this game.This game is very inspirational to me as a musician and indie game developer.  It is giving me a lot of ideas for my next game.Music and art style is a bit of an acquired taste.  I like it, but it may not be everyone's thing.  I recommend using a MIDI controller with a lot of knobs on it, and taking subtle approaches to the experience, because that is the way to go with this game."
