,Recommended,284260,18106036,"Posted: 19 September, 2015",all,Josko,"Ok, so basically, I rarely pay 10 euros for a game on Steam but this seemed like a worthy project to contribute to.Initially i found the game really well executed for the target audience it would have.This is actually not so much of a game as it is a series of prerendered interactive visualisations and music, this should be clear to anyone who doubts this.Anyhow, the music and sound selections are mostly really well picked and the visual effects are rendered in a very pleasant way, offering a ton of variation when you have control over what happens.I do find the selection of songs/stages still rather limited at the moment and not showing the maximal strenghts of the games appeal. Overall, the music hangs in a kind of adjustable steady flow which creates a calm, meditating sense of play but it can get a bit repetitive and too much in the ambient genre. Personally, I prefer the  stages that include a certain sense of advancement in them. the first and last stages portray this nicely and especially the selection of guest stages fare best in this matter.I hope the developers will find a way to bring some more content to the game or ideally create an editor for users to create more stages themselves. That would make the possibilities endless.Still it's a worthy and refreshing experience hard to be disliked!"
