76561197977862426,Recommended,284260,20152611,"Posted: 31 December, 2015",all,Fuscus,"This is absolutely the kind of thing to play when you want to just let the experience wash over you.On my first pass through, I had some real favorite soundscapes and some not-so-favorites. However, sitting down one evening using my headphones and much-larger-than-my-monitor television I found myself really enjoying every scene. I do sort of wish that the music/sound could be decoupled from the visuals in a few cases where I really liked the audio, but tweaking it to that state resulted in things like color schemes I didn't love. But! It's still lovely, even when the designers made choices I don't entirely agree with.And, let's be honest, this is exactly the sort of experience that most people will find pairs very well with recreational brain chemistry modification."
76561198072724649,Recommended,284260,20310587,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,BaronVonNukem,"Ten bucks for an experimental soundtrack that lets you control the ebb and flow of the music, 100% worth every penny."
,Recommended,284260,20316214,"Posted: 4 January, 2016",all,Sensual Lettuce,"I wouldn't consider this a game, but more of an audio visual experience. The experience is comprised of around 12 different stages, each of which have their own visual theme and music track. The way you play the game is by triggering disparate parts of the visual scene and audio track, melding them into a unique combination of all the elements. In writing it is slightly difficult to convey how the game works, but it is easy to grasp in practice and the effect is enchanting.This is not really a game that anyone needs, but it is a wonderful experience to have, especially if you have a good audio/visual setup in your gaming environment. I played this on a 120"" projected display with DTS sound and it blew my mind.Interestingly, Panoramical can be played with a MIDI controller (used for music production) as well as a gamepad or keyboard and mouse."
,Recommended,284260,20045926,"Posted: 28 December, 2015",all,python-b5,"Who came up with the idea of an interactive abstract art piece to modify to your heart's content, changing the sky and the water and the ground...if they exist? I mean, it IS abstract. Who knows what all that stuff is.The guests were great too. The disco-like triangle place with a strange pulsating red thing and a upbeat soundtrack, the floating city on the water with purple rings to dive through, the realistic-looking scrolling city...so beautiful.I'm yet to play inverted mode, and I've only played each scene once, but the time I've spent on this game so far were worth it.If you think a game needs a way to win, a way to die, and a way to score points, then don't get PANORAMICAL. But, like me, if you don't think a game needs that stuff, then get this game. Or is it a game? I'm not sure...But whatever. If your definition of a game is a picture you control, preferably a pretty one, then you'll love PANORAMICAL.It's perfect."
